{"article_id":"ovHApY5Uo8rAlhV3","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Staff at a Maryland newspaper have published a Friday edition","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"after a gunman killed five people and injured two more at the paper 's office .","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"`` We are putting out a damn paper tomorrow , ''","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"tweeted Chase Cook , a Capital Gazette reporter .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"Staff worked in the car park","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"to get the paper out .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"The gunman ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"who fired through a glass door into the newsroom on Thursday with a shotgun ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"was arrested afterwards .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"He has been charged with murder","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"and has a bail hearing shortly .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"A Capital Gazette reporter tweeted the charge sheet","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"which shows","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"that Jarrod Ramos was charged with five counts of first-degree murder .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"The suspect is reported to have unsuccessfully sued the newspaper group in 2012 for defamation .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"The paper tweeted the front page of their Friday paper as well as obituaries of their colleagues .","depth":4},{"id":16,"text":"First reports of the shooting came at 14:40 local time","depth":5},{"id":17,"text":"( 18:40 GMT )","depth":5},{"id":18,"text":"on Thursday .","depth":4},{"id":19,"text":"Journalists inside the building posted on social media","depth":5},{"id":20,"text":"as the gunman fired through the glass door of the office with a shotgun","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"and shot at staff inside .","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"An intern at the paper , Anthony Messenger , tweeted","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"as the attacker opened fire .","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"Fellow staff member Selene San Felice told CNN","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"her first reaction to the shooting had been to lie down under her desk .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"She tried to get out through a rear door","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"but it was locked .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"Crime reporter Phil Davis was also in the building","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"and told The Baltimore Sun","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"- part of the same media group as the Gazette -","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"that he and his colleagues had hidden under their desks .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"`` I do n't know","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"why he stopped","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"[ shooting ] , ''","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"he told the paper .","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"He described the scene as `` like a war zone ''","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"and tweeted about his experiences","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"as he waited to be interviewed by police .","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"County executive Steve Schuh told CNN","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"the suspect had been hiding under a desk in the building","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"when police officers arrived `` within 60 seconds ''","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"of receiving news of the incident .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"There was `` no exchange of fire '' ,","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"he added .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"`` This was a targeted attack on the Capital Gazette , ''","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"said William Krampf , deputy chief of Anne Arundel County Police .","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"He added","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"that the gunman had `` entered the building with a shotgun","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"and looked for his victims","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"as he walked through the lower level '' .","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"Speaking to reporters ,","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"Mr Krampf said","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"an item","depth":14},{"id":54,"text":"`` we believed to be an explosive device ''","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"had been found at the premises","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"and destroyed .","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"It turned out to be a smoke bomb ,","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"he said","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"Police say","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"they safely evacuated 170 people from the building ,","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"which housed 30 other businesses .","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"The Committee","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"to Protect Journalists","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"tweeted","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"that before the Maryland shooting , seven journalists had been killed in the US in relation to their work since 1992 .","depth":5},{"id":66,"text":"Most recently , TV reporter Alison Parker and cameraman Adam Ward were killed in 2015 during an interview in Moneta , Virginia .","depth":4},{"id":67,"text":"The Gazette reportedly wrote an article in 2011 about a woman","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"who said","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"Jarrod Ramos was stalking her ,","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"and he failed in his attempts","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"to sue the paper for defamation the following year .","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"Police did not ascribe any motive","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"after arresting him","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"following Thursday 's attack .","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"Ramos is scheduled for a bail hearing on Friday morning in Annapolis .","depth":4},{"id":76,"text":"Federal agencies ,","depth":5},{"id":77,"text":"including the FBI and the Bureau of Alcohol , Tobacco , Firearms and Explosives ,","depth":5},{"id":78,"text":"were involved in the response to the attack .","depth":4},{"id":79,"text":"Maryland governor Larry Hogan said on Twitter","depth":5},{"id":80,"text":"he was `` absolutely devastated ''","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"and was in contact with authorities .","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"President Donald Trump tweeted","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"that his `` thoughts and prayers '' were with the victims and their families .","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders later condemned the attack on `` innocent journalists","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"doing their job '' .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"The New York City Police Department","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"( NYPD )","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"it had deployed counterterrorism teams to media organisations in and around New York City as a precaution .","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"Mayor of Annapolis Gavin Buckley told the Guardian","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"he could not understand","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"how the paper `` could make someone that hostile '' .","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"`` If this is an attack on journalism","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"it is a sad state of affairs , ''","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"`` Because journalists , you do n't get paid enough","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"to put your life on the line ,","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"we 're not in some war zone ,","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"we 're not in some third-world country with a dictator . ''","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"Democratic senator Chris Van Hollen responded to a Gazette reporter on Twitter .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"Writer and alt-right figure Milo Yiannopoulos has faced criticism online","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"for writing","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"that he `` ca n't wait for the vigilante squads to start gunning journalists down '' .","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"Mr Yiannopoulos has defended himself on Facebook ,","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"saying","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"the message was `` a troll '' .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":213,"left":168,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":168,"left":122,"right":167,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":112,"right":121,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":112,"left":108,"right":111,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"